        "short_description": "CONFIGURATION FOR THE MRS FROM THE INTERNAL DESTINATION: 123 TIMEKEEPER",
        "u_description": "\u003Cp\u003Ewe have a configuration in CFG for the Material Requisition with a condition, when you choose the Internal Destination: 123 Time Keeper and the part requested is an uniform part, this combination \u00A0make that the Material requisition doesn\u0026#39;t require an authorization, we did it this way intentionally because we need that all deliveries from this warehouse be in real time.\u003C/p\u003E\r\n\u003Cp\u003E\u00A0\u003C/p\u003E\r\n\u003Cp\u003EYou can see the examples: MR 361 and 363, when the MR only has part of uniform, approval is not required.\u003C/p\u003E\r\n\u003Cp\u003E\u00A0\u003C/p\u003E\r\n\u003Cp\u003EWe need that this configuration can be migrated to Production but we want to know if we can add something else to this configuration, when the Internal Destination is 123 Time Keeper and an uniform part are chosen, can this combination make that the requisitioner only be able to see the timeKeeper Warehouse (TSS) \u00A0for the reserve?\u00A0\u003C/p\u003E\r\n\u003Cp\u003E\u00A0\u003C/p\u003E\r\n\u003Cp\u003EIn the current configuration in CFG when we choose an uniform part, it allows us to view any warehouse that has this part in inventory.\u003C/p\u003E\r\n\u003Cp\u003E\u00A0\u003C/p\u003E",
