                "Title": "comments",
                "PlainTextDescription": null,
                "RichTextDescription": "Hi All, Since all follow-ups have been sent to remind the incident and there is no feedback from the user so far, kindly inform your feedback before closing the ticket. The resolution for this issue is as follows. ------------------------------------------------------------------------------ Hi All, We observed that a similar case has been reported previously through the RF ticket number IN00012224. (no ID for the Carrix customer case portal) Through the above ticket number, the issue was reported to the IFS under the case CS0185490 and the below feedback has been provided. \u0022Server Error : Error while serializing contents\u0022 This error happens when the server cannot serialize the data to be sent to the client. A common cause is that one attribute\u0027s length exceeds the defined maxlength in the projection. In customer\u0027s environment, it was identified that some transactions have report comment which exceeds 100 characters. ReportComment attribute was only allowing 100 characters and error occurs due to attribute\u0027s length exceeds the defined maxlength in the projection. R\u0026amp;D has already provided the fix for this issue by increasing the maxlength to 4000 characters. You can get the fix from below versions. 22.2.14 - 22R2 SU14 23.1.7 - 23R1 SU7 23.2.0 - 23R2 GA 24.1E.0 - 24R1 EA\u0022 Therefore, first, kindly verify if the same issue was reported previously through IN00012224. If so, then you can mitigate the issue by getting one of the above fix. Hope this works. Let me know your feedback. Thanks, Lakshika.",
                "GenericHelpDeskComment": {
                    "commentId": "055e444ec35e02148550f04c0501314b",
                    "creationDate": "2024-05-22T05:48:29",
                    "createdBy": null,
                    "title": "comments",
                    "plainTextDescription": null,
                    "richTextDescription": "Hi All, Since all follow-ups have been sent to remind the incident and there is no feedback from the user so far, kindly inform your feedback before closing the ticket. The resolution for this issue is as follows. ------------------------------------------------------------------------------ Hi All, We observed that a similar case has been reported previously through the RF ticket number IN00012224. (no ID for the Carrix customer case portal) Through the above ticket number, the issue was reported to the IFS under the case CS0185490 and the below feedback has been provided. \u0022Server Error : Error while serializing contents\u0022 This error happens when the server cannot serialize the data to be sent to the client. A common cause is that one attribute\u0027s length exceeds the defined maxlength in the projection. In customer\u0027s environment, it was identified that some transactions have report comment which exceeds 100 characters. ReportComment attribute was only allowing 100 characters and error occurs due to attribute\u0027s length exceeds the defined maxlength in the projection. R\u0026amp;D has already provided the fix for this issue by increasing the maxlength to 4000 characters. You can get the fix from below versions. 22.2.14 - 22R2 SU14 23.1.7 - 23R1 SU7 23.2.0 - 23R2 GA 24.1E.0 - 24R1 EA\u0022 Therefore, first, kindly verify if the same issue was reported previously through IN00012224. If so, then you can mitigate the issue by getting one of the above fix. Hope this works. Let me know your feedback. Thanks, Lakshika."
                }
